# .claude/ holds Claude Code session caches, project transcripts, local plans, etc.
# But .claude/skills/ is shared content (skill definitions used by every agent
# in this repo) and MUST be tracked. Using /.claude/* (not .claude/) so git
# still descends into the dir to honor the !skills/ negation below.
/.claude/*
!/.claude/skills/
*.swp
*.swo
*~

